               <interp inst="t18480515-1441" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/18480515"></interp>
               <interp inst="t18480515-1441" type="date" value="18480515"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18480515-1441-charge-1" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-1441-18480515 t18480515-1441-offence-1 t18480515-1441-verdict-2"></join>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18480515-1441-charge-2" targOrder="Y" targets="def2-1441-18480515 t18480515-1441-offence-1 t18480515-1441-verdict-1"></join>
               <p>1441. <persName id="def1-1441-18480515" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1441-18480515" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1441-18480515" type="surname" value="DOWDING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1441-18480515" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JAMES DOWDING</hi>
                  </persName> and <persName id="def2-1441-18480515" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-1441-18480515" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1441-18480515" type="surname" value="HILLESLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1441-18480515" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JAMES HILLESLEY</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18480515-1441-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18480515-1441-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18480515-1441-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp>, stealing 18lbs. weight of copper, value 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; the goods of <persName id="t18480515-name-1422" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1422" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1422" type="surname" value="LOAT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1422" type="given" value="WILLIAM JOHN"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18480515-1441-offence-1 t18480515-name-1422"></join>William John Loat</persName>, their master.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PRENDERGAST</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480515-name-1423" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1423" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1423" type="surname" value="LOAT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1423" type="given" value="WILLIAM JOHN"></interp>WILLIAM JOHN LOAT.</persName>
                  </hi> I am a builder, at Clapham—Hillesley was my wagoner four or five months, and Dowding my gardener and odd-man. On 30th March I directed Hillesley to take the cart to Nine Elms; and on 6th April, in consequence of something I heard, I went to a stable on my pre<lb></lb>mises, and found a piece of copper, worth 7<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. or 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—I had not missed it; it had been in a closet or cupboard, in a shed, which was always locked—the padlock appeared locked and perfect—it was fastened by a secrew-staple, but a person could take it out and put it much in the same state that it was in before.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. ROBINSON.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Have you the copper here? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> This is it (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>)—I did not know how much there was in the place—probably I never should have missed any, but this had been the cover of a roof—this is a very common form for old copper to be in—Dowding has been in my service seven or eight years—I had a very hight opinion of him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did Hillesley drive the cart? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—he lived with his family, at Balham-hill—he has been bailed, and has surrendered to take his trial.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480515-name-1424" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1424" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1424" type="surname" value="MATTHEWS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1424" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES MATTHEWS.</persName>
                  </hi> I am a marine-store dealer, of Wandaworth. On 30th March, Hillesley came to my house a little after nine o'clock, and offered me this piece of copper for sale—I asked where he got it—he said it was no matter; there it was, if I chose to buy it—I said it would not suit me, he had better take it away again—he took it away—I informed the police.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Had you ever seen him before? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No—I am positive he is the man—I swear to the copper by some red paint on it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480515-name-1425" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1425" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1425" type="surname" value="SPICE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1425" type="given" value="ALFRED"></interp>ALFRED SPICE</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, V</hi> 41.) I received information from Mr. Matthews, and on 6th April went to a stable on Mr. Loat's premises with him and the sergeant, and this copper was found there—I afterwards took</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184805150166"></xptr>
               <p>Hillesley—I asked whether he knew anything about the copper—he said he knew nothing about anything—I afterwards showed him the copper—Mr. Loat told him he had better tell the truth—something was said, but I did not hear what.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480515-name-1426" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1426" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1426" type="surname" value="EMERSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1426" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT EMERSON</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-sergeant</hi>, 9 <hi rend="italic">V.</hi>) I found this copper on 6th of April—I spoke to Hillesley about it—Mr. Loat told him he had better tell the truth—I waited till Dowding came—Mr. Loat said to him, "I have been informed some copper has been taken from my premises, and you know something about it"—Dowding said, "By whom have you been informed"—Mr. Loat said, "By Hillesley"—Dowding said, "Bring him before me" Mr. Loat said, "He is safe in custody"—Dowding stood a minute or five, and then said, "If I tell the truth, will you forgive me?"—Mr. Loat said, "I have nothing to do with it"—Dowding stood a second or so and said, "I had better tell you the truth; I will show you how I got it"—he went to the shed door, unscrewed the staple and the lock came off; you could then open the door.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. ROBINSON.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Were you in uniform? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes; I had seen Dowding before, but had no conversation with him—I heard nothing said to him before about unscrewing the lock—I had no suspicion that that was the way it had been done—nothing had been said to Dowding about the staple till he went to it.</p>
               <p>(The prisoners received good characters, and a witness engaged to take Hillesley into his service.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">HILLESLEY</hi>—
<rs id="t18480515-1441-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18480515-1441-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18480515-1441-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="withRecommendation"></interp>
                     <hi rend="smallCaps">GUILTY</hi>.—<hi rend="italic">Recommended to mercy—</hi>
                  </rs>
                  <hi rend="italic">
                     <rs id="t18480515-1441-punishment-243" type="punishmentDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18480515-1441-punishment-243" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
